---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-07-02';
---

<BaseLayout title="Affiliate Disclosure" description="How VisaLang handles affiliate links and commercial recommendations." noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>What affiliate links are</h2>
        <p>Some links on VisaLang to preparation courses, textbooks, or tutoring services may be affiliate links. If you buy through them, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you.</p>

        <h2>How we use them</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Affiliate links appear only <strong>after</strong> the official-source section on a guide page.</li>
          <li>They are clearly labeled as "Advertisement", "Sponsored", or "Affiliate link".</li>
          <li>We only recommend products relevant to the route and language level.</li>
          <li>We never imply a paid product is required by the exam owner or government.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What an affiliate link never means</h2>
        <p>An affiliate link is not an official recommendation, a statement that a course is required, a promise of acceptance, or a promise of an exam or visa outcome. VisaLang provides independent, informational guidance only, not legal or immigration advice. Readers should verify with the local German mission or competent authority and, where relevant, the school, employer, professional body, exam owner, or authorised local test centre before considering any paid preparation option.</p>

        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p>Affiliate relationships do not influence our official-source guidance or our guide rankings. We prioritize official information over commercial recommendations.</p>

        <h2>Your trust</h2>
        <p>If an affiliate recommendation seems misleading or inaccurate, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>. We review and remove partners that violate our editorial standards.</p>

        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
